<article>
	<a name="about"></a>
	<header>
		<h2>About <small>Stuff you really want to know</small></h2>
	</header>

	<p>lfsworld.js is a small utility wrapper around <a href="https://github.com/spire-io/shred">Shred</a> to
	query <a href="http://www.lfsworld.net/">LFSWorld.net's</a> pubstats <a
		href="http://www.lfsforum.net/showthread.php?t=14480">API</a>.</p>
	<p>Tested and built for node, however as Shred supports the browser it may
	also work there. It is untested in that scenario at present.</p>

	<p>If you find bugs, or have issues with lfsworld.js please log an issue on
	github. Pull requests and patches are welcome. If you submit a patch please
	feel free to add your name and details to the package.json contributors key.</p>
</article>

<article>
	<a name="installation"></a>
	<header>
		<h2>Installation <small>Network fish</small></h2>
	</header>

	<code>npm install lfsworld.js</code>
</article>

<article>
	<a name="example"></a>
	<header>
		<h2>All-in-one Example <small>Hit the ground running</small></h2>
	</header>

<code>var lfsw = require('lfsworld.js');

var i = new lfsw({ idk: 'your-ident-key-here' });

i.getHosts(function(res) {

	if (res.isError())
	{
		console.error(res.raw);
		return;
	}

	console.log(res.data);

});
</code>
</article>

